# Adobe Commerce Drop-in SDK

## SDK Foundation

- **@dropins/tools** (~1.7.0): GraphQL client, event bus, initializers, UI components
- Use design tokens from SDK: colors, typography, spacing, shapes, grid
- Reference: https://experienceleague.adobe.com/developer/commerce/storefront/sdk/

## Design Tokens

Use CSS variables for consistency:
```css
var(--spacing-small)   /* 16px */
var(--spacing-medium)  /* 24px */
var(--spacing-large)   /* 64px */
var(--color-brand-500)
var(--color-neutral-100)
var(--type-body-1-default-font)
```

## SDK Utilities

- `classList` - CSS class management
- `debounce` - Limit function invocation frequency
- `deepmerge` - Deep object merging
- `getCookie` - Cookie value retrieval
- `getFormErrors` / `getFormValues` - Form handling
- `getPathValue` - Object path value extraction

## Event Bus

```javascript
import { events } from '@dropins/tools/event-bus.js';
events.on('event/name', handler);
events.emit('event/name', payload);
```

## GraphQL

Use `fetchGraphQl` from `@dropins/tools/fetch-graphql.js` for Commerce API calls. Configure endpoint via `setEndpoint()` and headers via `setFetchGraphQlHeader()`.
